# Design Tokens System

This file defines the visual language of the application. It does not define UI structure or components. It defines the system of values that UI is allowed to use.

This system is designed for Tailwind v4 (CSS-first architecture).

---

# 1. Token Architecture (Tailwind v4 model)

Design tokens are defined at CSS level using Tailwind v4 `@theme`.

- Tokens are the source of truth
- Tailwind utilities are consumers of tokens
- shadcn/ui consumes semantic tokens only

Rule:
- UI must not define its own visual language outside this system

---

# 2. Color System (Semantic Only)

Only semantic color roles are allowed in UI:

- background
- foreground
- muted
- muted-foreground
- primary
- secondary
- destructive
- border
- input
- ring

Rules:
- No hex values in UI
- No arbitrary color values
- No feature-specific color definitions
- No custom palettes per feature

Color must express meaning, not decoration.

---

# 3. Spacing System

Spacing must follow Tailwind v4 spacing scale derived from tokens.

Rules:
- Use consistent spacing scale across all features
- No arbitrary spacing values unless explicitly justified
- No feature-specific spacing systems

Forbidden:
- px-[13px]
- random spacing not aligned with scale

---

# 4. Radius System

Allowed radius scale:

- sm
- md
- lg
- xl

Rules:
- No custom radius outside system
- Consistency across components is mandatory
- UI should feel visually uniform across all features

---

# 5. Typography System

Typography must use Tailwind default scale or token-derived values.

Rules:
- No arbitrary font sizes
- No feature-specific typography rules
- Hierarchy must remain consistent across system

---

# 6. Shadow / Elevation System

- Shadows must be reusable and consistent
- No custom shadows per feature
- Elevation must follow system-level definitions only

Rule:
- Visual depth is a system property, not a feature decision

---

# 7. Tailwind Usage Policy

Tailwind is a utility layer, not a design authority.

Rules:
- Tailwind utilities must consume tokens, not define them
- No ad-hoc visual systems inside components
- No per-feature styling systems
- className must remain within system constraints

---

# 8. shadcn/ui Integration Rule

- shadcn/ui components must use semantic tokens only
- shadcn must not introduce custom visual rules
- all styling overrides must respect design system tokens

Rule:
- shadcn is a consumer of the token system, not a parallel system

---

# 9. Anti-Patterns

Forbidden patterns:

- hardcoded hex colors in components
- inconsistent spacing between features
- custom design systems inside features
- one-off visual decisions not aligned with tokens
- bypassing semantic color system
- uncontrolled arbitrary values in Tailwind

---

# 10. Consistency Rule

The UI must remain visually coherent across the entire system:

- same spacing logic everywhere
- same color semantics everywhere
- same radius scale everywhere
- same elevation system everywhere

Rule:
- consistency > local visual preference

---

# 11. System Philosophy

This design token system enforces:

- visual consistency
- scalable UI architecture
- predictable styling behavior
- separation between design intent and implementation
- long-term maintainability of UI language